tags: the things you come up with at 4am
summary: Came up with a new theory (which probably has been thought of before):
body:
Came up with a new theory (which probably has been thought of before):


Kylo (or one of the Knights of Ren) brought Finn from the Jedi Temple all those years ago when Finn was a child and put him in Storm Trooper training…so Finn trained with Luke (and Ben?) but doesn’t remember it.


This would explain the issue of the Storm Trooper paradox and why Finn may seem force sensitive and stand out from the other Storm Troopers.


Thoughts?

by SlytherinPirate

Ben Solo is an unhappy 16-year-old high school student who always seems to be disappointing everybody. His only escape is in his mind, where every night he dreams that he is a mystical space wizard named Kylo Ren who can use a superpower called The Force.
One day, he wakes up and discovers that he can now use The Force in real life! And when he gets to school, a new student has transferred in that Ben immediately recognizes as the fearsome general from his dreams, General Hux.

tags: even r2 has more confirmed kills than Boba Fett
summary: Hot take: in the films Boba Fett is less important to the Star Wars universe than Jar  Jar Binks
title: Hot take: in the films Boba Fett is less important to the Star Wars universe than Jar  Jar Binks
body:
Jar Jar:
- Leads The Jedi to Otoh Gunga so they are able to reach Theed in time to save the queen.
- Leads The Naboo to the Gungans and is thus indirectly responsible for lasting civil peace
- Has at least 3 confirmed kills including a tank during the battle of Naboo
- Votes the Chancellor emergency powers indirectly leading to the Clone Wars

Boba:
- Follows the Millennium Falcon a bit and snitches on the to the Empire
- Doesn’t even enter the room until Han has been disarmed
- Doesn’t even put Solo on his ship himself
- zero confirmed kills
- killed by a blind man
